article.headline: Cal Poly-SLO 102, Hawaii 89
article.story: HONOLULU -- Lorenzo Keeler scored 31 points and Cal Poly San Luis Obispo hit 11 3-pointers in a 102-89 victory over Hawaii in a BracketBuster game Saturday night. David Hanson added 18 points and Shawn Lewis had 17 for the Mustangs (10-16. Roderick Flemings scored a career-high 39 points for the Warriors (9-17), and Petras Balocka added 23 points and 16 rebounds. Cal Poly scored its most points since beating Long Beach State 103-88 on Feb. 8, 2001 and reached triple digits for the first time since a 100-79 victory over Portland State on Nov. 27, 2001. The Mustangs built a 23-point lead in the first half before Hawaii rallied to within 64-56 with less than 14 minutes to play. The Warriors, who lost their eighth straight, never got any closer. Cal Poly hit eight 3s in the first half and led 51-30 at intermission.
